# Mac light control plane (mandatory)

**Law:** `~/Desktop/MacLaw/MAC_HEALTH_AGENT_MANDATES_LOCKED.md` · `data/mac-law-mandatory-v1.json`  
**Cleanup:** `python3 scripts/mac_focus_cleanup_v1.py --json`

## One law

> **Mac observes and controls — cloud/API factories execute.**  
> No auto screenshot · no film render storm · no stacked session gates · no local motor drain.

## MUST keep ON (disk flags)

- `~/.sina/no-auto-screenshot-v1.flag`
- `~/.sina/auto-run-disabled-v1.flag` (unless ASF re-enables)
- `~/.sina/commercial-film-render-frozen-v1.flag`
- `~/.sina/mac-health-quiet-v1.flag`
- `~/.sina/config/visual_proof.json` → `enabled: false`

## MUST NOT on Mac

- Hub/factory `screencapture` loops (visual proof)
- Playwright film render while frozen
- `fbe_motor_delegate` storms (cap 8/15)
- Stacked `anti_staleness_auto_wire --tier session` (session-flight dedupe)
- Reading multi-GB hub logs into agent context

## When Mac is hot

1. Run `mac_focus_cleanup_v1.py` — enforces screenshot off · trims debug logs
2. Session gate uses **one** anti-staleness flight (dedupe)
3. Quit Cursor from DMG — reopen `/Applications/Cursor.app` if mandates say so
4. Cloud work stays on Railway/API — not local Python factory stack
